  "time_ut": 1657638979,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc7 \u0b85\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the President goes, the Prime Minister will be the next President",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has said that the Prime Minister should become the President as per the Constitution after the President announced his resignation.",
        "But he mentioned that the general opinion of the people and those involved in the protest is that the Prime Minister should step down and they do not know whether he will step down.",
        "He said this while commenting to the media after participating in the religious services held at Hunupitiya Kangarama Vihara for the former Prime Minister of Japan, Shinsho Abe.",
        "The former President also said that he had discussed with the protest activists and conveyed to the Speaker and all those responsible in the government the need to take their views into consideration.",
        "He warned that the country should be brought to a peaceful state by discussing with the people involved in the protest and taking steps within the framework of the constitution and if there is any delay, the country will get worse day by day."
      ],
